    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1334</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23T14:00:00+08:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Referring to my cable of December 18, 7 p.m., Japanese now demand appointment to
                    Tsingtao customs of forty-nine officials taken from Japanese customs
                    administration. This affects the treaty powers as such action would break up the
                    organization of Maritime Customs Service.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
